{
  "stem": "13584.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Poland, was always anti-Semitism, always.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I cannot say that the majority of people were anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some were-- couldn't care.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most of them couldn't care.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "A lot, a big percentage, were anti-Semitic.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In what capacity, in what extent, some were pointing, oh, here is a Jew.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "For example, when my father boarded a train-- it was a train to escape-- to escape Warsaw to go to Russia.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, I recall.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And even though he had a little bit bigger, big nose, but he didn't look Jewish, with blue eyes.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And he was not recognized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But one of his formal coworkers, or whatever, pointed, oh, He's a Jew.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Here is a Jew.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Polish police [INAUDIBLE] start to beat him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But he jumped into the wagon, into the, you know the wagon.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And he disappeared from [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And the train moved.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, so--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After the war, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] the anti-Semitism was there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But it was suppressed by the government.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Let me-- let me try to explain certain things.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Jews, especially those who came from Russia, who survived, most of them were trusted for the communist Polish government.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] A lot of them left for-- for Israel, for Palestine then, in 1946, 1947-- till 1950, Jews could leave Poland.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Some Jews did not leave.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They stood in Poland.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were staying in Poland.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "In Poland after the war-- after the war, there were, opened, 22 Yiddish schools.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the times of the Six-Day War, we had six schools say-- three schools, I'm sorry-- left in Poland.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Poland, the Polish government, communist government, let the Jews have two newspapers.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Then, it became one newspaper-- two in Yiddish, one in Polish.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
